<node id="全新但无盒子">
  <data key="d0">全新但无盒子</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">全新但无盒子 refers to the condition of a product that is brand new but does not include its original packaging. This description applies broadly to various items, including specific examples like a mug, indicating that while the product itself is in pristine condition, it lacks the box that typically accompanies new merchandise.

The term emphasizes that the product is new, ensuring potential buyers understand its quality, but it also clarifies that the absence of a box may affect its presentation or perceived value. Overall, 全新但无盒子 succinctly communicates the essential state of the product for sale, highlighting both its newness and the lack of packaging.&lt;SEP&gt;The condition of the product is described as brand new but without a box, indicating its state for potential buyers.</data>
