<node id="Conversation Record">
  <data key="d0">Conversation Record</data>
  <data key="d1">other</data>
  <data key="d2">The Conversation Record is a comprehensive documentation of interactions between buyers and sellers regarding products. It includes essential details such as the time of the conversation, session ID, user ID, product ID, and the roles of the participants, typically identifying one as the seller and the other as the buyer.

The record captures the content of messages exchanged during the dialogue, which may involve inquiries about the product, negotiations on price, and discussions about shipping information. Additionally, it provides insights into the product itself, including its price, description, and condition. The conversation record serves as a crucial tool for tracking the status of transactions and understanding the dynamics of buyer-seller interactions.

Overall, the Conversation Record is vital for maintaining a clear and organized account of product-related discussions, ensuring that all relevant information is readily accessible for future reference or analysis.&lt;SEP&gt;The conversation record contains details of a user interaction, including timestamps, user IDs, and product information.&lt;SEP&gt;The conversation record contains details of a dialogue including time, session ID, user ID, product ID, role, message content, related product, product price, product description, shipping information, and condition of the item.&lt;SEP&gt;The conversation record contains details of a chat session including time, session ID, user ID, product ID, seller role, message content, related product, product price, product description, shipping information, and condition.&lt;SEP&gt;The conversation record details a transaction involving a seller and a product, including timestamps and user IDs.</data>
